<div id="review_3878442067" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3878442067" />
    <a title="George K. Ilsley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4003368-george-k-ilsley"><img alt="George K. Ilsley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442467989p2/4003368.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3878442067?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="George K. Ilsley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="George K. Ilsley" href="/user/show/4003368-george-k-ilsley">George K. Ilsley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780679424529" href="/book/show/855714.The_Makioka_Sisters">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4003368-george-k-ilsley?shelf=modern-classic">modern-classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4003368-george-k-ilsley?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4003368-george-k-ilsley?shelf=japan">japan</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4003368-george-k-ilsley?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3878442067" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7468527228585716041">Some time ago, I saw a list of the best Japanese novels compiled by David Mitchell (of &quot;Cloud Atlas&quot; fame). The Makioka Sisters was the first book on the list of his favourites.<br/><br/>Naturally, I then read The Makioka Sisters and can see why it is considered a classic, and many people feel it deserves a place at the top of many lists. It is a quiet novel of forceful personalities, and the clash of what is felt to be traditional and the contrasting pull of what is seen to be necessary, or contemporary.</span>
  <span id="freeText7468527228585716041" style="display:none">Some time ago, I saw a list of the best Japanese novels compiled by David Mitchell (of "Cloud Atlas" fame). The Makioka Sisters was the first book on the list of his favourites.<br /><br />Naturally, I then read The Makioka Sisters and can see why it is considered a classic, and many people feel it deserves a place at the top of many lists. It is a quiet novel of forceful personalities, and the clash of what is felt to be traditional and the contrasting pull of what is seen to be necessary, or contemporary. <br /><br />The pre-World War II years in Japan were a potent stew of contrasts and conflicts — in the country and, as brilliantly illustrated here, within families. There are four Marioka sisters, and so, in effect, this novel is a type of quartet, with four voices, four characters who each have their own style, their own dreams and aspirations, and their own fate.<br /><br />Also, I learned it is a good idea to respect David Mitchell's book recommendations!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7468527228585716041" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


